1
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,200
So why exactly

2
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,120
did the family suddenly agree to surgery?

3
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:37,280
And on top of that,

4
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,120
a transapical TAVR.

5
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,439
I asked Liu Dong about it.

6
00:01:39,959 --> 00:01:40,680
It was Ouyang Da.

7
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:42,159
She secured

8
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,319
sponsorship from the valve manufacturer

9
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,239
and used a new product.

10
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,280
That's why the family and Director Lin

11
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:47,079
decided to go ahead.

12
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,400
Sponsorship is, of course,

13
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,239
good for the patient.

14
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,040
But neither a manufacturer

15
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:51,840
nor a distributor

16
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:53,439
can provide one-on-one sponsorship

17
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:54,519
to a specific patient.

18
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:55,400
That's against the rules.

19
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,840
Did they go through a third party?

20
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:57,959
Yes.

21
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,519
Through a foundation.

22
00:02:00,799 --> 00:02:02,079
Under the same eligibility criteria,

23
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,599
Yu Aizhu was the best-qualified candidate.

24
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,799
So she received it.

25
00:02:05,319 --> 00:02:06,439
Do you really think it was that coincidental?

26
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,560
Or was it earmarked for Yu Aizhu?

27
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,120
Does it matter?

28
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,599
As long as it helped the patient.

29
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,319
You had nothing to do

30
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,800
with the sponsorship, right?

31
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:16,120
Ouyang Da and Director Sheng

32
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:16,960
handled it, correct?

33
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
So I didn't need to get involved.

34
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,000
Exactly.

35
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:21,280
The surgery and the product

36
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,479
both passed through your hands.

37
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:24,680
What do you mean?

38
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,520
Are you saying Director Sheng wants to hurt me,

39
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:29,240
or that your ex-girlfriend does?

40
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:32,759
I told you,

41
00:02:33,599 --> 00:02:35,039
Ouyang Da will stop at nothing.

42
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:37,280
Even when there's no clinical need,

43
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,479
she'll create one.

44
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,159
Her priority isn't the patient.

45
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,000
It's profit.

46
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:42,280
There's nothing wrong with wanting to make money.

47
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,159
Do you even know who she is now?

48
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:50,719
Did you know she has a son?

49
00:02:55,479 --> 00:02:56,240
His name is Xiaosenlin.

50
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,280
He's five years old.

51
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:00,280
Restrictive cardiomyopathy.

52
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:10,800
When he was born,

53
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,919
the symptoms weren't obvious.

54
00:03:12,599 --> 00:03:13,759
He was hospitalized with pneumonia at three

55
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,520
and was finally diagnosed.

56
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:16,639
Medication is helping

57
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:17,840
reduce the strain on his heart,

58
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,319
but myocardial fibrosis is irreversible,

59
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,000
and his diastolic function

60
00:03:22,639 --> 00:03:23,560
is slowly deteriorating.

61
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:24,759
Mister,

62
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:27,199
the hospital squirrels

63
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:28,280
wake up very early,

64
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,800
because mornings here

65
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,599
begin at six o'clock.

66
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,240
Grandma's calling us.

67
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,680
Bye, doctor.

68
00:03:34,719 --> 00:03:35,360
Don't run.

69
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:36,000
You can't run.

70
00:03:36,599 --> 00:03:37,479
I've told you.

71
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,520
Walk slowly.

72
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:39,919
One,

73
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:40,719
two.

74
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:44,639
Didn't you wonder before

75
00:03:44,639 --> 00:03:45,599
why she got divorced?

76
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,719
It was because of Xiaosenlin.

77
00:03:50,199 --> 00:03:51,159
After he was diagnosed,

78
00:03:51,759 --> 00:03:53,000
her husband saw him as a burden

79
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,879
and divorced her.

80
00:03:56,439 --> 00:03:57,479
So now

81
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,400
she works herself to the bone

82
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,400
to pay for his treatment.

83
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,439
He's only five.

84
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:13,800
You know nothing about her,

85
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:15,919
so don't judge her.

86
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,120
I'm not the only one who needs to grow up.

87
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:20,839
You do too.

88
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,439
What about you?

89
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,120
Why did you stop being a doctor

90
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,959
and become a drug rep?

91
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,160
For the same reason many people switch careers.

92
00:04:55,519 --> 00:04:56,519
I wanted

93
00:04:56,519 --> 00:04:57,839
more time of my own

94
00:04:58,519 --> 00:04:59,279
and more money.

95
00:04:59,959 --> 00:05:00,600
That's not for you to decide.

96
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,279
To a patient's family,

97
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:02,639
as long as their loved one can live,

98
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,560
they'll pay anything,

99
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:05,040
even if it ruins them.

100
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,079
No one needs to coerce them.

101
00:05:08,439 --> 00:05:09,079
Director Zhou,

102
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:10,560
do you really have

103
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,680
such a low opinion of me?

104
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,839
Dr. Zhang is mad at me.

105
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:19,839
I'm not.

106
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,120
Please try to understand.

107
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:23,759
I have a family to support too.

108
00:05:24,639 --> 00:05:25,399
Besides,

109
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:27,079
wasn't that patient

110
00:05:27,079 --> 00:05:27,920
one your department had already rejected?

111
00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:29,240
Isn't this outcome

112
00:05:29,319 --> 00:05:30,560
good for the patient too?

113
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:33,600
The outcome is good, of course.

114
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:34,920
I'm happy for the patient

115
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,680
and her family.

116
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,040
But what do you mean

117
00:05:37,319 --> 00:05:38,600
by saying we rejected her?

118
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:40,199
That day,

119
00:05:40,199 --> 00:05:40,959
they clearly said

120
00:05:40,959 --> 00:05:41,959
they wouldn't accept surgery.

121
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:43,959
I misspoke.

122
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,759
That was my fault.

123
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:45,720
All right, all right.

124
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,439
Dr. Zhang,

125
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,800
please don't hold it against me.

126
00:05:49,319 --> 00:05:49,920
Manager Ouyang,

127
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,240
you don't need to apologize to me.

128
00:05:51,959 --> 00:05:52,759
I just feel

129
00:05:52,759 --> 00:05:53,560
it's unfair to Director Zhou.

130
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:54,920
The whole department's performance

131
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,600
and everyone's pressure

132
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,199
are now resting

133
00:05:56,199 --> 00:05:57,360
on his shoulders alone.

134
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,959
And Cardiac Surgery is coming on strong.

135
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:03,079
You're the same.

136
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:04,519
You turned around and went to them.

137
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:07,399
I had no choice.

138
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:08,920
I need to find a way to survive.

139
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,240
My handover period

140
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,199
is almost over.

141
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:12,759
I knew going to Director Zhou

142
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:14,680
would get me nowhere.

143
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:16,360
So I came to you

144
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,360
to see whether

145
00:06:17,399 --> 00:06:19,319
you could help me one last time.

146
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,360
Help you?

147
00:06:21,759 --> 00:06:22,560
You still don't know?

148
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,199
The director repaid hostility with kindness

149
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:25,600
and let you off.

150
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,240
Director,

151
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,000
has Maiampere

152
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,920
assigned a new representative?

153
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,120
Not yet.

154
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,759
We promised them a transition period,

155
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:36,759
so I haven't pressed them.

156
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,680
Call Qin Xiong.

157
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,360
Tell him there's no need to replace her.

158
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,839
But from now on, vet everything carefully.

159
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,519
No more breaches of principle.

160
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:52,600
Right.

161
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,480
Zhang Zhen called me just now.

162
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:55,879
I hadn't had time to tell you.

163
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:56,639
Ouyang,

164
00:06:57,439 --> 00:06:59,519
Zhou Xiaofeng is pretty funny.

165
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,279
Now he's coming back to make amends.

166
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,959
Do you think he's gone soft on you,

167
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,079
or does he see Cardiac Surgery as a threat

168
00:07:06,319 --> 00:07:07,720
and still needs you as a pawn?

169
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:09,639
I've worked with him for years.

170
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:10,759
I know him.

171
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,199
He may look

172
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:13,920
colder than anyone,

173
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,519
but deep down, he's softer than anyone.

174
00:07:15,759 --> 00:07:17,199
He gives everything to his patients,

175
00:07:17,519 --> 00:07:18,560
his colleagues and subordinates,

176
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,160
and his family and friends.

177
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:21,879
The only person he's hard on is himself.

178
00:07:22,439 --> 00:07:23,160
If he truly wanted

179
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,160
to play the part

180
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:24,959
of a ruthless man,

181
00:07:25,759 --> 00:07:27,160
would he be

182
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,040
in such a bind now?

183
00:08:05,439 --> 00:08:05,959
Director Lin,

184
00:08:06,199 --> 00:08:06,800
there seems to be

185
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,800
no ICU bed available.

186
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:09,920
What do we do?

187
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,319
Call Dr. Fang.

188
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:17,800
Xiaoran,

189
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,079
I have an emergency patient

190
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:19,839
coming out of surgery.

191
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:21,240
They say there are no ICU beds.

192
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:23,240
Right. Cardiac Surgery is full.

193
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:24,000
And unfortunately,

194
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,759
this week,

195
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:25,720
three patients in a row

196
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:26,800
had postoperative complications.

197
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,959
None can be transferred out yet.

198
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:29,399
With beds tied up,

199
00:08:29,399 --> 00:08:30,240
turnover has slowed.

200
00:08:30,639 --> 00:08:31,279
Okay, I understand.

201
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,360
This patient

202
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,679
can't stay in the OR.

203
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,759
If necessary,

204
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,200
we'll transfer Yu Aizhu

205
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,399
to the regular ward early.

206
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:38,000
No.

207
00:08:39,879 --> 00:08:40,480
I'll think of something else.

208
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:42,759
Call Director Zhou.

209
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:43,840
Okay.

210
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:47,200
Hello?

211
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:48,440
Do you have

212
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,480
any beds left in the CCU?

213
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:50,759
What's wrong?

214
00:08:51,039 --> 00:08:52,120
I have an emergency patient

215
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:52,960
coming out of surgery.

216
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:53,639
There's no bed.

217
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:55,080
If you can't make room either,

218
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,080
Yu Aizhu may have to be transferred

219
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,120
to the regular ward early.

220
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,039
Got it.

221
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,519
Got it.

222
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:08,360
Does Director Zhou want her transferred

223
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:08,960
or not?

224
00:09:15,519 --> 00:09:16,480
I'm hungry.

225
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:17,679
Hungry.

226
00:09:20,639 --> 00:09:21,360
Mom's really hungry.

227
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:21,919
Dad, look.

228
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:23,960
Looks good, right?

229
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,000
No rush, Mom. Here.

230
00:09:25,279 --> 00:09:25,960
Slowly. That's it.

231
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,360
Thanks for the bed.

232
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,200
Is it good?

233
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,519
Good.

234
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,519
Good.

235
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,360
I put the noodles in

236
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,399
just as the water began to bubble,

237
00:09:41,399 --> 00:09:42,200
exactly like you said.

238
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,759
And added just a little lard.

239
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:45,519
Smells good?

240
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:47,440
Good.

241
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:11,879
Working late again today?

242
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:16,639
Then let's eat together.

243
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,200
Forget it if you don't want any.

244
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,240
I'll have noodles.

245
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:31,960
Seafood noodles.

246
00:10:34,399 --> 00:10:34,879
Sure.

247
00:10:38,799 --> 00:10:39,240
Eat more.

248
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,360
Have some soup.

249
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:04,399
Director Zhou,

250
00:11:08,519 --> 00:11:09,919
have you seen Director Lin?

251
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:12,759
He's probably in surgery.

252
00:11:13,919 --> 00:11:14,519
No wonder

253
00:11:14,759 --> 00:11:16,279
he didn't answer my calls.

254
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,360
I'll wait here then.

255
00:11:19,559 --> 00:11:20,240
I'll give him the materials

256
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,240
when he's done.

257
00:11:21,399 --> 00:11:22,240
What materials?

258
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,080
About artificial hearts.

259
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,519
We talked a few days ago

260
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:27,840
about the latest biventricular assist device.

261
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,200
He was very interested.

262
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:31,039
The product materials are finally ready,

263
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:31,919
so I brought them over.

264
00:11:32,879 --> 00:11:34,360
You also represent a biventricular assist device?

265
00:11:35,039 --> 00:11:36,039
Not my company.

266
00:11:36,399 --> 00:11:37,679
It's another product.

267
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:39,559
It has more indications

268
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,440
and is smaller.

269
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:41,440
I thought,

270
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,720
maybe it could help Xiaorui.

271
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,440
It's always good to learn

272
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,440
about the latest developments.

273
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:46,480
One more option

274
00:11:46,679 --> 00:11:47,679
means one more hope.

275
00:11:48,919 --> 00:11:49,919
May I take a look?

276
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:50,919
Of course.

277
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,879
Why don't you wait in my office?

278
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,120
I'll have Lin Yi come pick it up.

279
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:17,159
Okay.

280
00:12:33,159 --> 00:12:33,679
What's wrong?

281
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:36,200
My shoes are soaked.

282
00:12:36,519 --> 00:12:37,080
My feet are freezing.

283
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:38,639
Sit down first.

284
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:43,840
You're crying because your feet are cold?

285
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,120
You don't understand.

286
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:48,039
When my feet are cold, my whole body feels awful.

287
00:12:48,519 --> 00:12:49,720
Every unhappy thing in the world

288
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:50,720
comes back to me,

289
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,480
and I'm miserable all day.

290
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,120
I can do it myself.

291
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,720
People say the stomach reflects emotions.

292
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:02,759
What,

293
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,679
are your feet emotional organs too?

294
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:07,600
I'm sick,

295
00:13:07,639 --> 00:13:08,840
and you still don't care about me.

296
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,000
Here.

297
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,360
This should cheer you up.

298
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:33,360
Sit down.

299
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:42,600
Thank you.

300
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,480
It's pouring outside.

301
00:14:02,679 --> 00:14:03,600
Why didn't you drive?

302
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:07,080
My dad took the car.

303
00:14:11,639 --> 00:14:12,279
Careful, it's hot.

304
00:14:13,159 --> 00:14:13,679
Thanks.

305
00:14:27,639 --> 00:14:28,159
Director Zhou,

306
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,600
thank you for giving me another chance.

307
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,279
This job

308
00:14:32,279 --> 00:14:33,399
means a lot to me.

309
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,399
I misunderstood you before.

310
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,080
Xiaoran told me

311
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,399
about Liang Mei.

312
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,240
It wasn't your fault.

313
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:46,960
And this time,

314
00:14:47,279 --> 00:14:48,639
for the patient with severe aortic stenosis,

315
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:49,879
transapical TAVR

316
00:14:49,879 --> 00:14:51,159
was the only option left.

317
00:14:51,559 --> 00:14:52,960
You know very well, Director Zhou,

318
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,240
that the procedure

319
00:14:54,399 --> 00:14:55,519
was extremely risky.

320
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,279
Other than Director Lin,

321
00:14:58,039 --> 00:14:59,000
I doubt anyone else

322
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,200
would have accepted the challenge.

323
00:15:04,039 --> 00:15:04,879
In any case,

324
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:06,919
the patient received funding,

325
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,360
and the surgery succeeded.

326
00:15:08,639 --> 00:15:09,440
That's a good outcome.

327
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,519
You also helped

328
00:15:11,519 --> 00:15:12,480
find a nursing home.

329
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,639
The family can finally breathe a little easier.

330
00:15:15,559 --> 00:15:16,960
We did what we could.

331
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,279
We all have parents.

332
00:15:46,039 --> 00:15:47,200
So you moved into sales

333
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,759
because of your child?

334
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,399
Director Lin told you?

335
00:15:56,799 --> 00:15:57,679
As an attending,

336
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,799
I only earned so much a month.

337
00:16:00,559 --> 00:16:02,519
Even if I eventually became an associate chief

338
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,360
or chief physician

339
00:16:04,879 --> 00:16:05,840
and earned more,

340
00:16:06,919 --> 00:16:07,639
I was afraid

341
00:16:07,639 --> 00:16:08,639
my son couldn't wait that long.

342
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:15,039
Sales is actually a good fit for me.

343
00:16:15,279 --> 00:16:16,799
I'm always among the first

344
00:16:16,799 --> 00:16:17,759
to learn about

345
00:16:17,879 --> 00:16:19,039
the latest technologies.

346
00:16:19,679 --> 00:16:20,720
That gives me peace of mind.

347
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:27,759
Actually,

348
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,600
when Senlin was diagnosed,

349
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,879
I blamed myself.

350
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,600
When I was pregnant,

351
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:34,799
I was serving as chief resident.

352
00:16:35,919 --> 00:16:37,120
I was so busy then,

353
00:16:37,519 --> 00:16:38,600
I barely knew day from night.

354
00:16:38,639 --> 00:16:39,639
How could they assign a pregnant woman

355
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,440
as chief resident?

356
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:42,240
It was my choice.

357
00:16:43,039 --> 00:16:44,240
At first, I didn't tell

358
00:16:44,919 --> 00:16:45,799
the hospital

359
00:16:45,799 --> 00:16:46,720
that I was pregnant.

360
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:47,480
I didn't want to miss the opportunity.

361
00:16:48,559 --> 00:16:50,080
Once I missed it,

362
00:16:50,399 --> 00:16:51,399
I might have had to wait another year,

363
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,159
or even two or three,

364
00:16:53,399 --> 00:16:54,639
before I could become an attending.

365
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:55,919
I couldn't accept that.

366
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,320
But later,

367
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,080
I realized

368
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:01,919
this is simply life.

369
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,639
You always have to make choices.

370
00:17:04,519 --> 00:17:05,759
Did you take him

371
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,079
for genetic testing?

372
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:11,200
It was a gene mutation.

373
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:14,480
Then his condition was just an accident.

374
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,680
It had nothing to do

375
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:19,720
with the choices you made.

376
00:17:19,759 --> 00:17:20,599
Right.

377
00:17:21,279 --> 00:17:21,880
I keep telling myself

378
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:24,039
to move forward.

379
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,599
Actually,

380
00:17:30,839 --> 00:17:31,400
you could have told me

381
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,319
all this earlier.

382
00:17:33,319 --> 00:17:34,400
Tell you what?

383
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,160
Was I supposed to cry

384
00:17:36,839 --> 00:17:38,359
and beg for sympathy?

385
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:39,720
That's not who I am.

386
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,160
Still as stubborn as ever.

387
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,079
This time,

388
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,680
you're not just pitying me, are you?

389
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,279
No.

390
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:57,720
It's because you're capable.

391
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:00,839
And because

392
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:03,400
I realized

393
00:18:05,319 --> 00:18:06,079
I had been prejudiced against you.

394
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,200
You admit it?

395
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,039
I do.

396
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:13,839
I used to think

397
00:18:14,839 --> 00:18:16,119
you were a sales rep

398
00:18:16,119 --> 00:18:17,319
who cared only about money.

399
00:18:18,079 --> 00:18:18,680
Now I know

400
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,960
why you work so hard.

401
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,599
Has Daji left?

402
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:25,400
Me?

403
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:31,440
Manager O-Ouyang.

404
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:32,359
Why are you here?

405
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:34,680
Well...

406
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,039
Weren't you going to

407
00:18:36,319 --> 00:18:37,279
give me some materials?

408
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:38,200
Yes.

409
00:18:38,359 --> 00:18:38,960
They're over there.

410
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:42,960
Take a look.

411
00:18:43,039 --> 00:18:43,839
If you have any questions,

412
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,039
message me anytime.

413
00:18:45,079 --> 00:18:45,839
I'll explain.

414
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:46,480
No problem.

415
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,440
I'll get going, Director Zhou.

416
00:18:52,839 --> 00:18:54,240
I asked them to prepare another pair of shoes.

417
00:18:54,559 --> 00:18:55,680
Would you like to change before leaving?

418
00:18:58,880 --> 00:18:59,759
No need.

419
00:19:00,039 --> 00:19:00,519
Thank you.

420
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,240
Why didn't you tell me

421
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,480
she was waiting in your office?

422
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:13,039
That's exactly what I wrote in the message.

423
00:19:15,519 --> 00:19:16,880
Did I interrupt you two?

424
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:20,720
No.

425
00:19:22,079 --> 00:19:22,519
Then why

426
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:23,559
did she run the moment she saw me?

427
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,279
Go ask her yourself.

428
00:19:26,839 --> 00:19:27,519
I'm not close to her.

429
00:19:27,599 --> 00:19:28,160
Why would I ask?

430
00:19:35,599 --> 00:19:36,039
What's this?

431
00:19:38,359 --> 00:19:39,519
The joint cardiac center clinic.

432
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,519
So it's officially approved?

433
00:19:43,559 --> 00:19:44,680
Nice.

434
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,240
Being a leader

435
00:19:46,279 --> 00:19:47,759
really gets things done.

436
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:49,680
That was fast.

437
00:19:50,519 --> 00:19:52,079
When we want to do anything,

438
00:19:52,119 --> 00:19:53,240
we have to submit an application,

439
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,200
hold discussions,

440
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:55,039
and wait for approval.

441
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,680
Enough. Stop talking nonsense.

442
00:19:58,119 --> 00:19:59,640
Now that it's approved, I want to start quickly.

443
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,240
Your schedule is fine, right, Director Lin?

444
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,119
My schedule

445
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,440
is fine,

446
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:07,279
but my condition isn't ideal.

447
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:09,880
Director Zhou,

448
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:12,079
could you make me a coffee?

449
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:23,759
Teacher,

450
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,200
for the patients and the department,

451
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,039
I truly want to build

452
00:20:27,039 --> 00:20:28,599
this one-stop platform.

453
00:20:30,119 --> 00:20:31,839
Didn't you also approve

454
00:20:32,119 --> 00:20:32,680
Zhou Xiaofeng's

455
00:20:33,079 --> 00:20:34,039
joint clinic?

456
00:20:34,519 --> 00:20:36,680
His clinic promotes collaboration.

457
00:20:37,279 --> 00:20:38,759
But your proposal

458
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:40,119
would funnel every patient

459
00:20:40,559 --> 00:20:41,599
into your department.

460
00:20:42,519 --> 00:20:44,240
The difference in vision is obvious.

461
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,160
I'm not saying

462
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,559
your proposal is bad.

463
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:50,440
I just think

464
00:20:51,319 --> 00:20:53,559
Zhou Xiaofeng is gaining momentum.

465
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:55,880
There's no need

466
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:58,279
to make things so tense with him.

467
00:20:59,240 --> 00:20:59,880
I won't.

468
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:01,279
Good.

469
00:21:02,759 --> 00:21:03,440
Then take this proposal back

470
00:21:03,839 --> 00:21:05,759
and think it through again.

471
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,000
All right?

472
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:15,640
Dr. Ye,

473
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,680
push 500 milliliters of IV fluids.

474
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,480
Are you kidding me?

475
00:21:21,039 --> 00:21:22,160
I wrote it wrong. Just correct it.

476
00:21:23,319 --> 00:21:24,440
Could you stop making

477
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,720
such basic mistakes?

478
00:21:25,839 --> 00:21:26,720
Be more careful.

479
00:21:27,039 --> 00:21:28,319
Nurses are busy too.

480
00:21:28,599 --> 00:21:29,680
Basic mistake?

481
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:34,400
Then tell me,

482
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:35,680
what counts as an advanced mistake?

483
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:39,720
Xiao Ye.

484
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,400
Doctors write orders,

485
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,680
and nurses carry them out.

486
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:44,279
Besides, this was

487
00:21:44,279 --> 00:21:45,359
an obvious typo.

488
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,400
You could have simply corrected it.

489
00:21:46,839 --> 00:21:47,640
Dr. Ye,

490
00:21:48,359 --> 00:21:49,240
I am not obligated

491
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,599
to correct your mistakes.

492
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:51,640
Then don't ask.

493
00:21:53,359 --> 00:21:54,519
Just do your own job.

494
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,960
All right.

495
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:07,440
Don't be upset.

496
00:22:08,079 --> 00:22:09,119
In our line of work,

497
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:09,960
isn't it normal

498
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:11,119
to suffer a little unfairness?

499
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:12,960
I already get blamed by patients,

500
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,599
and now doctors push me around too.

501
00:22:14,799 --> 00:22:16,359
What gives her the right to talk to me like that?

502
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:17,640
Are nurses servants?

503
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:18,960
It was clearly her mistake.

504
00:22:19,359 --> 00:22:20,400
Who's a servant?

505
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,519
Head Nurse.

506
00:22:22,279 --> 00:22:23,279
What's going on?

507
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:24,839
Crying and arguing

508
00:22:25,119 --> 00:22:26,240
during working hours.

509
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,000
What kind of behavior is that?

510
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,039
Head Nurse,

511
00:22:30,119 --> 00:22:30,720
I won't accept this.

512
00:22:31,799 --> 00:22:32,519
Director Zhou.

513
00:22:47,319 --> 00:22:47,880
Head Nurse.

514
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:49,559
Do you have a moment?

515
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:50,759
I only need two minutes.

516
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,359
Of course.

517
00:22:54,519 --> 00:22:55,039
Come in.

518
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:02,680
Would you like something to drink?

519
00:23:05,359 --> 00:23:06,160
No, thank you.

520
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:06,799
I'll only say a few words.

521
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,039
Then I'll leave.

522
00:23:08,039 --> 00:23:08,839
Director Zhou, I joined

523
00:23:11,559 --> 00:23:12,599
the Cardiac Center

524
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:14,359
after you left for Guizhou.

525
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:15,519
At the time,

526
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:16,279
your predecessor, Director Wang Feng,

527
00:23:16,279 --> 00:23:17,680
was close to retirement.

528
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:18,720
His health wasn't good,

529
00:23:18,759 --> 00:23:19,599
and he lacked energy.

530
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,279
So

531
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:21,119
we in Nursing

532
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,400
took on as much clinical work

533
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,599
as we could.

534
00:23:23,599 --> 00:23:24,640
He also respected us.

535
00:23:25,279 --> 00:23:26,279
But

536
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,160
that can't be a long-term solution.

537
00:23:28,519 --> 00:23:30,000
Everyone has their own duties.

538
00:23:30,079 --> 00:23:31,240
So

539
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:31,880
the boundaries need to be clarified.

540
00:23:32,039 --> 00:23:33,279
Clear responsibilities are good.

541
00:23:35,359 --> 00:23:36,920
But what exactly

542
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:37,960
are you referring to?

543
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:38,759
For example,

544
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,000
except in emergencies,

545
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,920
nurses should no longer accept

546
00:23:42,119 --> 00:23:43,000
verbal orders.

547
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:43,680
For tests, medications, and procedures,

548
00:23:44,359 --> 00:23:45,319
doctors must issue

549
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,400
written orders.

550
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,759
Also,

551
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:48,440
when it comes to

552
00:23:48,799 --> 00:23:49,279
basic vital-sign monitoring,

553
00:23:49,279 --> 00:23:50,799
doctors can't simply

554
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,000
wait for nurses

555
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,000
to alert them.

556
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,039
You should also

557
00:23:55,039 --> 00:23:56,200
make regular rounds yourselves.

558
00:23:57,359 --> 00:23:59,000
That includes perioperative education.

559
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,799
Doctors should handle that too.

560
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,960
It helps earn

561
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:02,720
the patient's trust.

562
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:05,680
I agree that

563
00:24:06,039 --> 00:24:07,240
doctors and nurses

564
00:24:07,839 --> 00:24:08,880
shouldn't have

565
00:24:09,319 --> 00:24:10,640
a superior-subordinate relationship.

566
00:24:11,119 --> 00:24:12,079
Of course not.

567
00:24:12,559 --> 00:24:14,160
We're equal partners.

568
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:14,920
So

569
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,359
many informal practices

570
00:24:16,839 --> 00:24:18,000
need to be standardized.

571
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:21,960
I understand what you mean.

572
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:23,640
How about this:

573
00:24:23,839 --> 00:24:25,039
I'll first look into the situation,

574
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:25,960
see what can be improved,

575
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:26,599
and then come back

576
00:24:26,759 --> 00:24:27,759
to ask for your advice.

577
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:28,799
You're too kind.

578
00:24:29,319 --> 00:24:30,720
Sorry to disturb your break.

579
00:24:30,799 --> 00:24:31,279
I'll go now.

580
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:42,960
Has everyone recently

581
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:44,200
had some conflict with Nursing?

582
00:25:00,359 --> 00:25:01,119
So,

583
00:25:02,599 --> 00:25:04,079
you wrote the wrong order,

584
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,039
refused to admit it,

585
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,480
and blamed the nurse?

586
00:25:09,079 --> 00:25:10,319
She was aggressive

587
00:25:10,319 --> 00:25:11,119
and wouldn't let it go.

588
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:12,920
She's only a nurse.

589
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,440
What do you mean, "only a nurse"?

590
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,480
What did I tell you last time?

591
00:25:17,079 --> 00:25:18,559
What gives you the right to look down on nurses?

592
00:25:19,319 --> 00:25:20,279
Go apologize now.

593
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:21,319
If you're unwilling

594
00:25:21,319 --> 00:25:22,079
to change your attitude

595
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,240
and respect your colleagues,

596
00:25:25,799 --> 00:25:26,759
you can leave right now.

597
00:25:27,519 --> 00:25:29,559
X-Xiao Ye,

598
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:30,720
we actually get along

599
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,119
very well with the nurses.

600
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,079
You haven't been here long,

601
00:25:33,559 --> 00:25:34,240
so you may not understand.

602
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:35,559
The nurses work

603
00:25:35,559 --> 00:25:36,519
extremely hard.

604
00:25:37,079 --> 00:25:38,279
Experienced nurses

605
00:25:38,519 --> 00:25:39,960
can often spot

606
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:40,680
abnormalities before we do.

607
00:25:40,799 --> 00:25:42,119
We're grateful for that.

608
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:43,799
Privately,

609
00:25:43,799 --> 00:25:45,039
we buy one another milk tea

610
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,119
or coffee

611
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,240
and exchange small treats.

612
00:25:47,759 --> 00:25:48,960
Even when minor conflicts arise,

613
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:50,359
we don't let them become personal.

614
00:25:50,519 --> 00:25:51,039
Right?

615
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:01,519
Your hand.

616
00:26:02,839 --> 00:26:03,400
Stop picking at it.

617
00:26:04,079 --> 00:26:05,000
You'll damage the table.

618
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:17,519
Xiao Ye,

619
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,319
maybe I spoke too harshly.

620
00:26:21,119 --> 00:26:22,440
But you need to understand:

621
00:26:23,119 --> 00:26:23,920
if you can't

622
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:24,920
let go of your arrogance

623
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,000
and learn to respect your teammates,

624
00:26:29,359 --> 00:26:29,839
then I believe

625
00:26:29,839 --> 00:26:31,279
you're still far

626
00:26:32,519 --> 00:26:33,720
from being a qualified doctor.

627
00:26:40,559 --> 00:26:41,079
Go.

628
00:26:58,079 --> 00:26:58,559
Director,

629
00:26:59,160 --> 00:26:59,880
I'll speak with her

630
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:00,880
properly later.

631
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,519
I've already spoken to her.

632
00:27:02,839 --> 00:27:04,359
I don't understand why she's so stubborn.

633
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:06,160
Xiao Ye is actually

634
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:07,039
very talented.

635
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,839
Gifted people

636
00:27:09,279 --> 00:27:11,000
are often a little eccentric.

637
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,920
One Lin Yi is already enough for me.

638
00:27:15,359 --> 00:27:16,640
Now there's a younger one too.

639
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:19,680
Still,

640
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:21,599
what Head Nurse Shen said that day

641
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:23,119
was emotional,

642
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,079
but she had a point.

643
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:26,559
Doctors and nurses

644
00:27:26,599 --> 00:27:27,480
do need

645
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,720
a better communication mechanism

646
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:30,319
and clearer boundaries.

647
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,400
Find out

648
00:27:33,519 --> 00:27:33,920
exactly where

649
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:35,039
the gray areas are

650
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,440
and report back quickly.

651
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:37,599
Yes, Director.

652
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,640
Sister Yalan,

653
00:27:47,839 --> 00:27:48,640
I honestly didn't expect

654
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,559
this incident to cost us

655
00:27:49,559 --> 00:27:50,480
the Popular Department plaque.

656
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:51,279
It's a rotating plaque.

657
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:54,039
It's supposed to rotate.

658
00:27:54,279 --> 00:27:55,559
Right?

659
00:27:55,599 --> 00:27:56,079
It's fine.

660
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:57,079
We'll win it back next time.

661
00:27:57,319 --> 00:27:58,759
But it had been hanging here

662
00:27:59,000 --> 00:27:59,720
for so long.

663
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,519
It's all because of you-know-who.

664
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:01,920
I'm leaving.

665
00:28:02,599 --> 00:28:03,160
Do you need something, Dr. Ye?

666
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,640
Xiaojing, I'm sorry.

667
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:25,720
My attitude was poor that day.

668
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:27,640
I apologize.

669
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:28,400
I wouldn't dare accept it.

670
00:28:30,559 --> 00:28:31,759
We nurses deserve

671
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,359
to be ordered around.

672
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,440
How could I accept an apology from Dr. Ye?

673
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,039
When did I

674
00:28:36,599 --> 00:28:37,440
order you around?

675
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,559
I...

676
00:28:39,759 --> 00:28:40,119
Anyway, I apologized.

677
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,359
No.

678
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:50,079
Fine.

679
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:52,599
Two stubborn mules.

680
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:53,759
Quickly.

681
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:06,720
He has sudden, severe chest pain.

682
00:29:09,119 --> 00:29:10,160
Dadong.

683
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:10,599
We're at the hospital.

684
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:11,720
It's okay.

685
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:13,359
It's okay.

686
00:29:13,799 --> 00:29:14,200
I'm here.

687
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,200
Don't be afraid.

688
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:16,039
Hurry.

689
00:29:16,319 --> 00:29:16,839
Quickly.

690
00:29:18,079 --> 00:29:18,519
Don't fall asleep.

691
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,200
Don't be afraid.

692
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,880
The family should wait outside.

693
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,279
Okay.

694
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:26,799
Okay.

695
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:27,440
He doesn't look good.

696
00:29:34,599 --> 00:29:35,640
Chest pain and shortness of breath.

697
00:29:35,799 --> 00:29:36,759
It could be acute left-sided heart failure again.

698
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:38,119
I'm on my way.

699
00:29:38,319 --> 00:29:38,880
Director.

700
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:43,480
Have the blood tests been done?

701
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:44,559
The results are back.

702
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:45,960
D-dimer is markedly elevated.

703
00:29:51,039 --> 00:29:52,160
Highly suspicious for acute pulmonary embolism.

704
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:53,480
Arrange an echocardiogram

705
00:29:53,799 --> 00:29:54,519
and a CT pulmonary angiogram.

706
00:29:54,559 --> 00:29:54,920
Okay.

707
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:55,640
Dadong,

708
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:56,079
don't be nervous.

709
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:58,079
We'll run some tests first.

710
00:29:58,440 --> 00:29:58,839
He had only just improved.

711
00:29:59,039 --> 00:29:59,920
How did he get a pulmonary embolism?

712
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:07,920
Are his lungs failing too?

713
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,200
Please sit down.

714
00:30:09,519 --> 00:30:10,880
The heart and lungs affect each other.

715
00:30:11,119 --> 00:30:11,599
His cardiac function was already poor,

716
00:30:12,119 --> 00:30:13,720
so the lungs can be affected too.

717
00:30:13,799 --> 00:30:15,119
On top of that, he's been bedridden for a long time.

718
00:30:15,279 --> 00:30:16,400
That makes lower-extremity venous thrombosis

719
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:17,839
more likely

720
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:19,319
and increases the risk of pulmonary embolism.

721
00:30:19,839 --> 00:30:21,640
There are several contributing factors.

722
00:30:21,799 --> 00:30:23,240
The fastest and most effective option now

723
00:30:23,559 --> 00:30:24,799
is catheter-directed thrombus fragmentation

724
00:30:24,799 --> 00:30:26,279
and aspiration.

725
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:27,720
Director Zhou will do it himself.

726
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:28,440
You can rest assured.

727
00:30:29,119 --> 00:30:29,519
Okay.

728
00:30:30,519 --> 00:30:31,240
We'll follow your advice.

729
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:44,640
Begin thrombectomy.

730
00:31:11,319 --> 00:31:11,880
Give some fluids.

731
00:31:15,079 --> 00:31:15,839
Hello, operating room.

732
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:18,160
Is Director Sheng Nian there?

733
00:31:18,799 --> 00:31:19,640
Director Sheng is in surgery.

734
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:20,359
May I ask who's calling?

735
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:21,599
This is Xiao Pu,

736
00:31:21,599 --> 00:31:22,480
the duty officer

737
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,279
from the China Organ Transplant Response System.

738
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:24,960
We have an urgent notification.

739
00:31:25,359 --> 00:31:26,160
The system shows

740
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:27,240
a potential organ donor

741
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,000
in this city.

742
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:30,000
The criteria for brain death have been met.

743
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:31,240
Among the first group

744
00:31:31,240 --> 00:31:32,240
of candidates

745
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:33,039
released for preliminary allocation,

746
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:33,960
Lu Dadong

747
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:34,960
from Dongli Hospital's

748
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:35,680
Cardiac Surgery Department ranks first.

749
00:31:36,759 --> 00:31:37,920
That's wonderful news, Director.

750
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,079
Finding a matching donor heart

751
00:31:40,319 --> 00:31:41,599
so quickly

752
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:43,279
is harder than winning the lottery.

753
00:31:43,799 --> 00:31:44,359
That's great.

754
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:45,480
Notify Director Lin immediately.

755
00:31:45,799 --> 00:31:46,200
Okay.

756
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:48,400
Understood.

757
00:31:48,799 --> 00:31:49,319
Assess

758
00:31:50,559 --> 00:31:51,319
Lu Dadong's condition as soon as possible

759
00:31:51,319 --> 00:31:52,119
and determine whether he's fit for transplant.

760
00:31:52,279 --> 00:31:53,640
Reply within one hour.

761
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,640
The preliminary allocation notice

762
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:55,400
has been issued by the system.

763
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,240
Move quickly.

764
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:56,880
Dr. Fang,

765
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:57,960
that's an extremely tight timeline.

766
00:31:58,599 --> 00:31:59,480
We have to reply within an hour.

767
00:31:59,519 --> 00:32:00,640
From organ procurement

768
00:32:00,839 --> 00:32:01,680
to transplantation,

769
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:02,720
there's a limited cold ischemia window.

770
00:32:02,759 --> 00:32:04,160
Six hours at most.

771
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,119
Otherwise, at best,

772
00:32:05,839 --> 00:32:07,000
a precious donor heart is wasted.

773
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:07,839
At worst,

774
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:09,279
the transplant may fail,

775
00:32:09,519 --> 00:32:10,759
leading to graft failure

776
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:11,720
and the recipient's death.

777
00:32:12,319 --> 00:32:13,039
Is he currently

778
00:32:13,039 --> 00:32:13,799
fit for transplant?

779
00:32:14,319 --> 00:32:15,720
Pulmonary embolism is a contraindication.

780
00:32:16,279 --> 00:32:17,119
Acute pulmonary embolism

781
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:18,000
is only a relative contraindication.

782
00:32:18,079 --> 00:32:18,720
He needs to be assessed.

783
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:20,799
How did it go?

784
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:21,680
Was the thrombectomy successful?

785
00:32:23,359 --> 00:32:24,799
It was difficult, but overall successful.

786
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:25,759
We can basically confirm

787
00:32:25,759 --> 00:32:26,200
he won't need

788
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:26,799
ECMO again.

789
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:27,880
I'll be finished soon.

790
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:29,440
Estimate this for me:

791
00:32:29,519 --> 00:32:30,519
four or five hours after the procedure,

792
00:32:30,519 --> 00:32:31,519
could he undergo a heart transplant?

793
00:32:36,799 --> 00:32:37,559
A donor heart has become available.

794
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,400
It depends on his hemodynamics.

795
00:32:44,599 --> 00:32:45,480
His right ventricular function

796
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,079
is currently acceptable.

797
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:49,480
Under normal circumstances,

798
00:32:50,359 --> 00:32:51,079
it should be possible.

799
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,279
Among the first five

800
00:33:23,279 --> 00:33:24,359
candidates listed by the system,

801
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:25,599
the first and fifth

802
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:27,079
are both registered

803
00:33:27,079 --> 00:33:27,519
with Dongli's Heart Transplant Center.

804
00:33:28,119 --> 00:33:29,519
The other three are from other centers.

805
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:30,519
If Lu Dadong

806
00:33:30,519 --> 00:33:31,759
can't be confirmed for transplant,

807
00:33:31,839 --> 00:33:32,960
we'll have to consider the next candidates.

808
00:33:33,279 --> 00:33:34,279
The fact that Lu Dadong ranks first

809
00:33:34,279 --> 00:33:35,640
means he's the most critically ill.

810
00:33:36,599 --> 00:33:37,960
Now that a suitable donor is available,

811
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:38,519
we must not

812
00:33:38,519 --> 00:33:39,440
give up lightly.

813
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,559
Otherwise, he may not last much longer.

814
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:41,960
How is he now?

815
00:33:42,839 --> 00:33:43,799
The thrombectomy went well.

816
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:45,160
But he developed hypoxemia

817
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:45,960
in the ICU,

818
00:33:46,119 --> 00:33:46,839
so we intubated him.

819
00:33:47,519 --> 00:33:48,440
What does his family think?

820
00:33:48,759 --> 00:33:49,880
They want the transplant more than anything.

821
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,039
Good.

822
00:33:51,119 --> 00:33:51,759
If he develops

823
00:33:51,759 --> 00:33:52,880
any adverse symptoms,

824
00:33:53,079 --> 00:33:54,559
we must do everything possible

825
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:55,599
to intervene and stabilize him.

826
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:57,000
Once the donor heart reaches our center,

827
00:33:57,759 --> 00:33:59,079
we absolutely cannot let it slip away.

828
00:34:03,839 --> 00:34:04,799
His oxygenation is improving well.

829
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,440
According to Lin Yi's estimate,

830
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,400
there's a very good chance

831
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:09,159
he'll recover enough within four or five hours.

832
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:11,559
A donor heart is incredibly rare.

833
00:34:11,880 --> 00:34:12,599
We must seize

834
00:34:12,599 --> 00:34:13,280
this opportunity for Dadong.

835
00:34:13,599 --> 00:34:15,079
When Liang Mei heard there was a donor,

836
00:34:15,119 --> 00:34:16,280
she laughed and cried with joy.

837
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:17,440
It's fortunate

838
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:18,199
you insisted on not giving him

839
00:34:18,199 --> 00:34:19,119
an LVAD back then.

840
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,719
Now the cost of transplantation

841
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:21,599
shouldn't be as much of a concern.

842
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,800
You said there were two patients on the list.

843
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:24,440
Who's the other one?

844
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:28,039
I sent the recipient list

845
00:34:28,199 --> 00:34:28,800
to the group chat.

846
00:34:29,519 --> 00:34:30,559
Director, I need to make a call.

847
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:40,800
Brother.

848
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,719
Is the fifth patient Xiaorui?

849
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:15,239
I can't believe it.

850
00:35:15,599 --> 00:35:16,559
He's only been listed for just over a month,

851
00:35:16,559 --> 00:35:17,519
and he's already fifth.

852
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:19,159
I thought he'd be much farther down.

853
00:35:19,719 --> 00:35:21,159
The order of transplant candidates

854
00:35:21,239 --> 00:35:22,239
changes according to

855
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:22,960
the urgency of their condition

856
00:35:23,199 --> 00:35:24,440
and donor compatibility.

857
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:25,159
It's different every time.

858
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:26,280
But no matter what,

859
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:28,760
at least there's finally hope.

860
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:30,039
How is Lu Dadong now?

861
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:33,920
After the thrombectomy,

862
00:35:34,199 --> 00:35:35,079
his hemodynamics stabilized

863
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:36,920
and his oxygen saturation improved.

864
00:35:37,079 --> 00:35:37,920
He may develop reperfusion injury,

865
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:39,679
so we need to observe him.

866
00:35:39,719 --> 00:35:40,679
But based on

867
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:41,280
his current condition,

868
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:42,199
there's no active bleeding,

869
00:35:42,679 --> 00:35:43,840
and overall he's improving.

870
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,159
That's good.

871
00:35:46,239 --> 00:35:46,760
There's an update.

872
00:35:51,559 --> 00:35:52,360
The donor's family

873
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:56,800
is wavering in their grief

874
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:58,280
and can't bring themselves to consent.

875
00:35:58,719 --> 00:35:59,920
We're doing everything we can

876
00:36:00,079 --> 00:36:01,960
to communicate with them.

877
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:05,800
How could...

878
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:11,880
How could the family change their minds

879
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:13,039
at a time like this?

880
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:16,199
If they can't reach an agreement,

881
00:36:17,559 --> 00:36:18,519
then Lu Dadong...

882
00:36:19,159 --> 00:36:20,199
Their feelings

883
00:36:20,199 --> 00:36:21,119
are understandable.

884
00:36:21,559 --> 00:36:22,599
Look at it another way:

885
00:36:23,159 --> 00:36:24,480
it gives Lu Dadong

886
00:36:24,639 --> 00:36:26,000
more time to recover.

887
00:36:34,039 --> 00:36:34,679
Hello, Director Sheng.

888
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:40,400
All right.

889
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,079
I'll come over now.

890
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:44,320
The candidates at the other centers

891
00:36:44,360 --> 00:36:45,440
have also responded.

892
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:46,599
The second-ranked patient

893
00:36:46,599 --> 00:36:47,400
died two days ago.

894
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,119
The third-ranked patient

895
00:36:49,159 --> 00:36:50,039
is doing well with an artificial heart,

896
00:36:50,079 --> 00:36:51,519
so transplantation has been deferred.

897
00:36:52,039 --> 00:36:53,000
The fourth-ranked patient

898
00:36:53,079 --> 00:36:54,159
still has reservations

899
00:36:54,199 --> 00:36:54,800
about the transplant itself

900
00:36:55,039 --> 00:36:55,679
and has declined.

901
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,440
So the patient originally ranked fifth

902
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:00,880
is now effectively second.

903
00:37:09,159 --> 00:37:10,000
Xiao Guo

904
00:37:10,079 --> 00:37:11,400
hasn't yet confirmed in the system

905
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:13,079
that Lu Dadong will accept the transplant.

906
00:37:18,199 --> 00:37:20,880
I think we should discuss this further.

907
00:37:21,719 --> 00:37:22,960
The transplant window

908
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:23,679
is extremely narrow.

909
00:37:24,079 --> 00:37:24,960
If Lu Dadong

910
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:25,880
doesn't recover in time,

911
00:37:26,159 --> 00:37:26,880
will this opportunity

912
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:27,920
be wasted?

913
00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:29,840
This really does require

914
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:30,559
careful consideration.

915
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:32,559
Once we confirm acceptance

916
00:37:32,559 --> 00:37:33,480
in the allocation system,

917
00:37:33,719 --> 00:37:34,239
if the patient

918
00:37:34,239 --> 00:37:35,519
fails to recover fully afterward,

919
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,119
withdrawing the confirmation

920
00:37:37,159 --> 00:37:38,039
will be very complicated.

921
00:37:38,199 --> 00:37:39,400
It will take a great deal of explanation,

922
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:40,079
and we'll also have to submit

923
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,519
a detailed report

924
00:37:41,519 --> 00:37:42,719
to the health commission.

925
00:37:43,159 --> 00:37:44,480
It wastes time

926
00:37:45,599 --> 00:37:46,280
and delays everything.

927
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:48,639
So,

928
00:37:48,679 --> 00:37:49,800
should we speak

929
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:50,639
with Lu Dadong's family

930
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:52,559
about giving up the transplant?

931
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:56,599
At the same time, as a precaution,

932
00:37:57,079 --> 00:37:58,119
we should notify

933
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,719
Lin Xirui, currently fifth on the list,

934
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:00,679
to come to the hospital and wait.

935
00:38:01,239 --> 00:38:02,440
Complete all necessary tests.

936
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,280
If Lu Dadong

937
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:05,800
doesn't improve over the next few hours,

938
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:07,639
Lin Xirui can step in immediately,

939
00:38:08,239 --> 00:38:08,719
so the donor heart

940
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:09,800
won't be wasted.

941
00:38:10,559 --> 00:38:11,639
That does make sense.

942
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:14,400
Of course,

943
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,440
the backup candidate may

944
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:16,159
make the trip for nothing.

945
00:38:16,639 --> 00:38:17,440
So that possibility

946
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:18,440
must be explained to the family in advance.

947
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:19,320
Otherwise,

948
00:38:19,599 --> 00:38:20,320
the greater the hope,

949
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:21,199
the greater the disappointment.

950
00:38:21,639 --> 00:38:22,599
It will be. Don't worry.

951
00:38:23,119 --> 00:38:23,880
I'll get back to work.

952
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:24,840
If there's any new information,

953
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:25,480
I'll update everyone

954
00:38:25,639 --> 00:38:26,480
in the group chat.

955
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:27,360
Thank you.

956
00:38:33,719 --> 00:38:34,159
Xiao Lin,

957
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:36,280
come here.

958
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:55,199
Is this real?

959
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,239
We found a match this quickly?

960
00:38:58,400 --> 00:38:59,239
I didn't expect it either.

961
00:39:02,119 --> 00:39:03,079
That's wonderful, Brother Yi.

962
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,079
Don't get too excited.

963
00:39:04,559 --> 00:39:05,000
Take it easy.

964
00:39:06,159 --> 00:39:06,960
Let me finish.

965
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:10,000
Although a donor matches you,

966
00:39:12,599 --> 00:39:13,559
you're not first in line.

967
00:39:15,800 --> 00:39:17,079
The patient ahead of you

968
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:18,960
is currently in poor condition.

969
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,559
After discussion,

970
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:25,239
the hospital wants you to be admitted and wait.

971
00:39:27,239 --> 00:39:27,840
Are you willing?

972
00:39:31,039 --> 00:39:31,639
Of course.

973
00:39:33,519 --> 00:39:34,599
I'll wait at the hospital.

974
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:40,440
But

975
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:43,960
if the patient ahead of you improves

976
00:39:44,719 --> 00:39:45,639
and his symptoms stabilize,

977
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:47,440
the donor heart will go to him.

978
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:53,400
We may have come for nothing.

979
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:56,679
I understand, Brother Yi.

980
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:04,039
Even this tiny bit of hope

981
00:40:04,679 --> 00:40:05,960
already makes me very happy.

982
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:07,280
I'll go pack now.

983
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:09,639
I should bring

984
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:13,880
all my previous reports, right?

985
00:40:14,119 --> 00:40:14,760
Yes.

986
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:16,000
And a power bank,

987
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,039
a charger,

988
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:18,519
and the cup Xiaoran gave me.

989
00:40:20,199 --> 00:40:21,519
Brother Yi,

990
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:23,519
my dad waited so long

991
00:40:24,039 --> 00:40:25,519
before a donor match was found.

992
00:40:25,519 --> 00:40:26,119
And I got one almost immediately.

993
00:40:27,159 --> 00:40:28,239
I'm already very lucky.

994
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,280
No matter what,

995
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,199
the donor heart should go to Xiaorui.

996
00:40:35,639 --> 00:40:37,079
It's so rare to find a matching donor.

997
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:49,679
We should keep it for him.

998
00:40:50,119 --> 00:40:51,320
But...

999
00:40:59,119 --> 00:40:59,480
Lu Dadong ranks ahead of him.

1000
00:41:01,119 --> 00:41:02,559
Then there's nothing we can do.

1001
00:41:03,679 --> 00:41:04,519
He's unlucky.

1002
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,320
He suddenly developed a pulmonary embolism,

1003
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:07,280
which is indeed

1004
00:41:08,039 --> 00:41:09,000
a contraindication to transplantation.

1005
00:41:09,519 --> 00:41:10,639
Is it an absolute contraindication

1006
00:41:11,119 --> 00:41:12,039
or a relative one?

1007
00:41:12,039 --> 00:41:13,000
There isn't

1008
00:41:13,559 --> 00:41:14,719
a strict standard.

1009
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:15,639
Whether we're conservative or aggressive,

1010
00:41:16,679 --> 00:41:18,039
there's room for judgment.

1011
00:41:19,119 --> 00:41:20,239
Right?

1012
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:21,360
If they ask later,

1013
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,800
we can provide

1014
00:41:25,039 --> 00:41:26,199
a reasonable explanation.

1015
00:41:26,199 --> 00:41:26,960
Whether he's fit for surgery

1016
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:30,599
depends on clinical judgment.

1017
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:32,599
His current condition

1018
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:34,800
is right on the borderline.

1019
00:41:35,079 --> 00:41:36,440
We have the final say.

1020
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:41,719
Let's go, Brother Yi.

1021
00:41:55,719 --> 00:41:56,440
I'm packed.

1022
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:57,599
All right, Ms. Ouyang.

1023
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,119
I'll call you

1024
00:42:07,199 --> 00:42:07,920
after I've read it.

1025
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:08,559
Okay. Thank you.

1026
00:42:15,719 --> 00:42:16,280
Xiaorui.

1027
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:19,079
Sister Xiaomei.

1028
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,400
It really is you.

1029
00:42:21,119 --> 00:42:22,639
How have you been? Any better?

1030
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:23,360
I'm doing okay.

1031
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:24,639
How is Brother Dongzi?

1032
00:42:26,599 --> 00:42:28,280
He had an acute pulmonary embolism yesterday.

1033
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,280
Director Zhou performed an intervention,

1034
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:32,400
and he's now in the ICU.

1035
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:33,360
Don't worry.

1036
00:42:33,920 --> 00:42:34,960
Director Zhou is very skilled.

1037
00:42:35,639 --> 00:42:36,960
Dr. Xiaoran is in the ICU too.

1038
00:42:37,559 --> 00:42:38,800
Brother Dongzi will recover soon.

1039
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:40,719
Yes.

1040
00:42:41,519 --> 00:42:42,440
We finally found

1041
00:42:42,440 --> 00:42:43,480
a suitable donor heart.

1042
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:45,519
I'm just afraid

1043
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:47,840
he won't recover quickly enough

1044
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:49,400
and the contraindication won't resolve,

1045
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:50,719
so he'll miss

1046
00:42:50,719 --> 00:42:51,800
this transplant opportunity.

1047
00:42:53,559 --> 00:42:53,880
He...

1048
00:42:54,239 --> 00:42:56,440
Brother Dongzi...

1049
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:57,800
found a matching donor?
